        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:17PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Corydon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corydon, New Middletown, Laconia, Central, Evans Landing, and
Dogwood.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
